1.Go inside the folder by using terminal and write the command npx i -y...
2.Now go inside the terminal and write the command npm i express...
3.Now use nodemon for the automatic loading   
             --for that go inside the package.json folder and write   "start": "node index.js",
              "dev": "nodemon index.js"
              --If you write npm run dev to start the server...


create 5 files--a)Configs--all constant things are in this file .
                b)Models--All the properties if the function in this file.
                c)controller--All the function are in this file.
                d)Routes--routes contain the path of all the file .
                e).env-- enviroment file contains the port number of the file.and database url.

.now use npm i dotenv for importingthe env fole into an object.
